---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro'
---

<ProjectLayout
  badge="Control Systems · 2024"
  title="3-DOF Self-Balancing Platform — Stewart-Inspired Design."
  description="A 3-axis attitude control platform using PID + LQR control and real-time sensor fusion — built from scratch with custom control software and mechatronic design."
  coverImage="/portfolio/images/plat1.webp"
  coverAlt="3-DOF Self-Balancing Platform on test bench"
  ogImage="https://alesso-24.github.io/portfolio/images/plat1.webp"
  meta={[
    { label: 'Role',     value: 'Full-Stack Engineer (HW + SW)' },
    { label: 'Platform', value: 'Arduino Mega · MPU6050 · 3× Servos' },
    { label: 'Control',  value: 'PID + LQR · Kalman Filter · I²C' },
    { label: 'Tools',    value: 'Fusion 360 · C++ · Python · MATLAB' },
  ]}
>

  <!-- Pull quote -->
  <blockquote class="pull-quote" data-reveal>
    <p>"The gap between a working controller in MATLAB and a real platform that stays balanced is exactly where mechatronics engineering lives."</p>
  </blockquote>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- Demo Video -->
  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>Watch It Balance.</h2>
  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    Three axes. One MPU6050. 50ms control cycles. Watch the platform self-correct
    in real-time against deliberate perturbations — a live demonstration of closed-loop
    attitude control working as designed.
  </p>

  <div data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100" class="video-embed">
    <iframe
      src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/88SjHziDrIY"
      title="3-DOF Self-Balancing Platform — Control System Demo"
      allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
      allowfullscreen
      loading="lazy"
    ></iframe>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>Why This Problem is Hard.</h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    Building a single-axis pendulum that balances is a textbook exercise. Building
    a 3-DOF platform with coupled axes, real servo non-linearities, and I²C latency
    from sensor to actuator — that's where real control theory meets physical constraints.
  </p>
  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100">
    The challenge: a single IMU on the platform needs to feed three independent servo
    controllers, all without introducing phase lag that destabilizes the loop. The servo
    bandwidth, Kalman filter update rate, and PID cycle time had to be carefully matched
    to produce stable behavior across all three axes simultaneously.
  </p>

  <div class="stat-highlight" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="140">
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:clamp(16px,3vw,40px);">
      {[
        { num: '50ms', label: 'Control cycle time' },
        { num: '3-DOF', label: 'Axes controlled simultaneously' },
        { num: '±2°', label: 'Steady-state error target' },
      ].map(({ num, label }) => (
        <div style="border-top: 2px solid #2540c0; padding-top: 16px;">
          <div style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif; font-size:clamp(28px,3.5vw,52px); color:#2540c0; line-height:1; margin-bottom:8px;">{num}</div>
          <p style="margin:0; font-size:13px; color:#6f6a5f; letter-spacing:0.04em;">{label}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>System Architecture.</h2>

  <div class="tech-grid" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">01</div>
      <h3>Sensor Fusion Layer</h3>
      <p>MPU6050 gyro + accelerometer data fed into a discrete Kalman filter — delivering
      clean roll/pitch/yaw estimates free of gyroscopic drift and accelerometer noise.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">02</div>
      <h3>Dual-Mode Control</h3>
      <p>PID for setpoint tracking during commissioning; LQR for optimal disturbance rejection
      once the state-space model was validated. Both modes switch at runtime.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">03</div>
      <h3>Mechatronic Design</h3>
      <p>Fusion 360 chassis designed for minimal servo arm coupling. Geometry chosen to
      decouple roll, pitch, and yaw axes — making the math in the controller match reality.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Platform image grid -->
  <div data-reveal style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:clamp(12px,2vw,24px); margin: clamp(32px,5vh,56px) 0;">
    <div style="border-radius:14px; overflow:hidden; box-shadow:0 20px 50px -24px rgba(37,64,192,0.4);">
      <img src="/portfolio/images/plat2.webp" alt="Self-balancing platform — top view"
           loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%; height:auto; display:block;" />
    </div>
    <div style="border-radius:14px; overflow:hidden; box-shadow:0 20px 50px -24px rgba(234,106,46,0.35);">
      <img src="/portfolio/images/plat3.webp" alt="Self-balancing platform — side view"
           loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%; height:auto; display:block;" />
    </div>
  </div>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  .pull-quote {
    border-left: 3px solid #2540c0;
    margin: clamp(32px,5vh,56px) 0;
    padding: clamp(16px,2.5vw,24px) clamp(20px,3vw,32px);
    background: #efe7d8;
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
  }
  .pull-quote p {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    font-size: clamp(17px, 1.9vw, 24px);
    line-height: 1.4; color: #211f1a; font-style: italic;
  }
  .video-embed {
    position: relative; width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9;
    border-radius: 18px; overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 32px 80px -28px rgba(37,64,192,0.35);
    margin: clamp(20px,3vh,32px) 0 clamp(32px,5vh,56px);
    background: #211f1a;
  }
  .video-embed iframe { position: absolute; inset: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none; }
  .tech-num {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif; font-size: 32px;
    color: #2540c0; line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
</style>
